29 SUMMARY
3300 This bill makes necessary technical changes to update the statutes governing the
3311 Department of Administrative and Financial Services, Office of Information Technology
3322 to align with recent statutory updates and best practices. The bill does the following.
33 1. It allows the Chief Information Officer to have an authorized designee in certain
34 instances.
35 2. It includes certain definitions to align with the recently enacted definition of
36 "cyberattack" and updates terminology to reflect national best practices for cybersecurity
37 and information security.
38 3. It updates language regarding the mission of the office to reflect the bill's
39 terminology changes.
40 4. It updates a provision of statute regarding competitive bidding to allow the office to
41 procure information technology products or services necessary to detect, prevent and
42 respond to cyberattacks.
